Tom,<br><br>
I am in agreement.  Spitting is something that debases a human being.  It places him or her at the lowest contemptible level.  Even as a child I couldn't spit on anyone.  Being an old country boy my training didn't offer many options.  My grandfather always said turn the other cheek, but remember you only have two.  I know I should have more tolerance, but in this particular case I don't.  It has nothing to do whether it is a protestor or not.  Equal opportunity.<br><br>
My response to you concerning Cook was driven by a value I have never compromised.  I never take a hit at a man's religion no matter what I think of him.  I put that up there with spitting.  I make no judgement between a man and his God.  If I misunderstood then I apologize.  I just feel that Cook is completely honest and as such deserves our respect.<br><br>
My comment was short because I respect you and I wanted you to know that I disapproved<br><br>
Peace<br>

